#. <section class="sutta" id="mn33"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "mn33:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 33"
msgstr "Middle Discourses 33"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn33:0.2"
msgid "Mahāgopālakasutta"
msgstr "The Longer Discourse on the Cowherd"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya1"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.220"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "mn33:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "mn33:1.2"
msgid ""
"ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery."

msgctxt "mn33:1.3"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "mn33:1.4"
msgid "“bhikkhavo”ti."
msgstr "“Mendicants!”"

msgctxt "mn33:1.5"
msgid "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Venerable sir,” they replied."

msgctxt "mn33:1.6"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya2"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
#. VAR: phātiṃ kātuṃ → phātikattuṃ (bj, pts1) | phātikātuṃ (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "mn33:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Ekādasahi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgato gopālako abhabbo gogaṇaṃ "
"pariharituṃ phātiṃ kātuṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, a cowherd with eleven factors can’t maintain and expand a herd "
"of cattle."

msgctxt "mn33:2.2"
msgid "Katamehi ekādasahi?"
msgstr "What eleven?"

#. VAR: hāretā → sāṭetā (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "mn33:2.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, gopālako na rūpaññū hoti, na lakkhaṇakusalo hoti, na "
"āsāṭikaṃ hāretā hoti, na vaṇaṃ paṭicchādetā hoti, na dhūmaṃ kattā hoti, na "
"titthaṃ jānāti, na pītaṃ jānāti, na vīthiṃ jānāti, na gocarakusalo hoti "
"anavasesadohī ca hoti. Ye te usabhā gopitaro gopariṇāyakā te na "
"atirekapūjāya pūjetā hoti."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a cowherd doesn’t know form, is unskilled in characteristics, "
"doesn’t pick out flies’ eggs, doesn’t dress wounds, doesn’t smoke out pests, "
"doesn’t know the ford, doesn’t know when they’re satisfied, doesn’t know the "
"trail, is not skilled in pastures, milks dry, and doesn’t show extra respect "
"to the bulls who are fathers and leaders of the herd."

msgctxt "mn33:2.4"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho, bhikkhave, ekādasahi aṅgehi samannāgato gopālako abhabbo gogaṇaṃ "
"pariharituṃ phātiṃ kātuṃ."
msgstr ""
"A cowherd with these eleven factors can’t maintain and expand a herd of "
"cattle."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya3"></a>
msgctxt "mn33:3.1"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, bhikkhave, ekādasahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu abhabbo "
"imasmiṃ dhammavinaye vuddhiṃ virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ āpajjituṃ."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, a mendicant with eleven qualities can’t achieve growth, "
"improvement, or maturity in this teaching and training."

msgctxt "mn33:3.2"
msgid "Katamehi ekādasahi?"
msgstr "What eleven?"

msgctxt "mn33:3.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na rūpaññū hoti, na lakkhaṇakusalo hoti, na "
"āsāṭikaṃ hāretā hoti, na vaṇaṃ paṭicchādetā hoti, na dhūmaṃ kattā hoti, na "
"titthaṃ jānāti, na pītaṃ jānāti, na vīthiṃ jānāti, na gocarakusalo hoti, "
"anavasesadohī ca hoti. Ye te bhikkhū therā rattaññū cirapabbajitā "
"saṃghapitaro saṃghapariṇāyakā te na atirekapūjāya pūjetā hoti."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant doesn’t know form, is unskilled in characteristics, "
"doesn’t pick out flies’ eggs, doesn’t dress wounds, doesn’t smoke out pests, "
"doesn’t know the ford, doesn’t know satisfaction, doesn’t know the trail, is "
"not skilled in pastures, milks dry, and doesn’t show extra respect to senior "
"mendicants of long standing, long gone forth, fathers and leaders of the "
"Saṅgha."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya4"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "mn33:4.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na rūpaññū hoti?"
msgstr "And how does a mendicant not know form?"

#. VAR: sabbaṃ rūpaṃ → etthantare pāṭho 17A11:155
msgctxt "mn33:4.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu yaṃ kiñci rūpaṃ sabbaṃ rūpaṃ ‘cattāri mahābhūtāni, "
"catunnañca mahābhūtānaṃ upādāyarūpan’ti yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant doesn’t truly understand that all form is the four "
"primary elements, or form derived from the four primary elements."

msgctxt "mn33:4.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na rūpaññū hoti. (1)"
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant doesn’t know form."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya5"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "mn33:5.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na lakkhaṇakusalo hoti?"
msgstr "And how is a mendicant not skilled in characteristics?"

msgctxt "mn33:5.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ‘kammalakkhaṇo bālo, kammalakkhaṇo paṇḍito’ti "
"yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant doesn’t understand that a fool is characterized by "
"their deeds, and an astute person is characterized by their deeds."

msgctxt "mn33:5.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na lakkhaṇakusalo hoti. (2)"
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant isn’t skilled in characteristics."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya6"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.221"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "mn33:6.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na āsāṭikaṃ hāretā hoti?"
msgstr "And how does a mendicant not pick out flies’ eggs?"

msgctxt "mn33:6.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu uppannaṃ kāmavitakkaṃ adhivāseti, nappajahati na "
"vinodeti na byantī karoti na anabhāvaṃ gameti. Uppannaṃ byāpādavitakkaṃ … pe "
"… uppannaṃ vihiṃsāvitakkaṃ … pe … uppannuppanne pāpake akusale dhamme "
"adhivāseti, nappajahati na vinodeti na byantī karoti na anabhāvaṃ gameti."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant tolerates a sensual, malicious, or cruel thought that’"
"s arisen. They tolerate any bad, unskillful qualities that have arisen. They "
"don’t give them up, get rid of them, eliminate them, and obliterate them."

msgctxt "mn33:6.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na āsāṭikaṃ hāretā hoti. (3)"
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant doesn’t pick out flies’ eggs."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya7"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "mn33:7.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na vaṇaṃ paṭicchādetā hoti?"
msgstr "And how does a mendicant not dress wounds?"

msgctxt "mn33:7.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā nimittaggāhī hoti "
"anubyañjanaggāhī."
msgstr ""
"When a mendicant sees a sight with their eyes, they get caught up in the "
"features and details."

msgctxt "mn33:7.3"
msgid ""
"Yatvādhikaraṇamenaṃ cakkhundriyaṃ asaṃvutaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhādomanassā "
"pāpakā akusalā dhammā anvāssaveyyuṃ, tassa saṃvarāya na paṭipajjati, na "
"rakkhati cakkhundriyaṃ, cakkhundriye na saṃvaraṃ āpajjati."
msgstr ""
"Since the faculty of sight is left unrestrained, bad unskillful qualities of "
"desire and aversion become overwhelming. They don’t practice restraint, they "
"don’t protect the faculty of sight, and they don’t achieve its restraint."

msgctxt "mn33:7.4"
msgid "Sotena saddaṃ sutvā … pe …"
msgstr "When they hear a sound with their ears …"

msgctxt "mn33:7.5"
msgid "ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā … pe …"
msgstr "smell an odor with their nose …"

msgctxt "mn33:7.6"
msgid "jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā … pe …"
msgstr "taste a flavor with their tongue …"

msgctxt "mn33:7.7"
msgid "kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā … pe …"
msgstr "feel a touch with their body …"

msgctxt "mn33:7.8"
msgid "manasā dhammaṃ viññāya nimittaggāhī hoti anubyañjanaggāhī."
msgstr ""
"know a thought with their mind, they get caught up in the features and "
"details."

msgctxt "mn33:7.9"
msgid ""
"Yatvādhikaraṇamenaṃ manindriyaṃ asaṃvutaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhādomanassā "
"pāpakā akusalā dhammā anvāssaveyyuṃ, tassa saṃvarāya na paṭipajjati, na "
"rakkhati manindriyaṃ, manindriye na saṃvaraṃ āpajjati."
msgstr ""
"Since the faculty of the mind is left unrestrained, bad unskillful qualities "
"of desire and aversion become overwhelming. They don’t practice restraint, "
"they don’t protect the faculty of the mind, and they don’t achieve its "
"restraint."

msgctxt "mn33:7.10"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na vaṇaṃ paṭicchādetā hoti. (4)"
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant doesn’t dress wounds."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya8"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "mn33:8.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na dhūmaṃ kattā hoti?"
msgstr "And how does a mendicant not smoke out pests?"

msgctxt "mn33:8.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu yathāsutaṃ yathāpariyattaṃ dhammaṃ na vitthārena "
"paresaṃ desetā hoti."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant doesn’t teach others the Dhamma in detail as they "
"learned and memorized it."

msgctxt "mn33:8.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na dhūmaṃ kattā hoti. (5)"
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant doesn’t smoke out pests."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya9"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "mn33:9.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na titthaṃ jānāti?"
msgstr "And how does a mendicant not know the ford?"

msgctxt "mn33:9.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ye te bhikkhū bahussutā āgatāgamā dhammadharā "
"vinayadharā mātikādharā, te kālena kālaṃ upasaṅkamitvā na paripucchati, na "
"paripañhati:"
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant doesn’t from time to time go up to those mendicants "
"who are very learned—knowledgeable in the scriptures, who have memorized the "
"teachings, the Vinaya, and the outlines—and ask them questions:"

msgctxt "mn33:9.3"
msgid "‘idaṃ, bhante, kathaṃ?"
msgstr "‘Why, sir, does it say this?"

msgctxt "mn33:9.4"
msgid "Imassa ko attho’ti?"
msgstr "What does that mean?’"

msgctxt "mn33:9.5"
msgid ""
"Tassa te āyasmanto avivaṭañceva na vivaranti, anuttānīkatañca na "
"uttānīkaronti, anekavihitesu ca kaṅkhāṭhānīyesu dhammesu kaṅkhaṃ na "
"paṭivinodenti."
msgstr ""
"Those venerables don’t clarify what is unclear, reveal what is obscure, and "
"dispel doubt regarding the many doubtful matters."

msgctxt "mn33:9.6"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na titthaṃ jānāti. (6)"
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant doesn’t know the ford."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya10"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "mn33:10.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na pītaṃ jānāti?"
msgstr "And how does a mendicant not know satisfaction?"

msgctxt "mn33:10.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye desiyamāne na "
"labhati atthavedaṃ, na labhati dhammavedaṃ, na labhati dhammūpasaṃhitaṃ "
"pāmojjaṃ."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant, when the teaching and training proclaimed by the "
"Realized One are being taught, finds no joy in the meaning and the teaching, "
"and finds no joy connected with the teaching."

msgctxt "mn33:10.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na pītaṃ jānāti. (7)"
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant doesn’t know satisfaction."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya11"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "mn33:11.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na vīthiṃ jānāti?"
msgstr "And how does a mendicant not know the trail?"

msgctxt "mn33:11.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant doesn’t truly understand the noble eightfold path."

msgctxt "mn33:11.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na vīthiṃ jānāti. (8)"
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant doesn’t know the trail."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya12"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.222"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "mn33:12.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na gocarakusalo hoti?"
msgstr "And how is a mendicant not skilled in pastures?"

msgctxt "mn33:12.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cattāro satipaṭṭhāne yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant doesn’t truly understand the four kinds of mindfulness "
"meditation."

msgctxt "mn33:12.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na gocarakusalo hoti. (9)"
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant is not skilled in pastures."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya13"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "mn33:13.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu anavasesadohī hoti?"
msgstr "And how does a mendicant milk dry?"

msgctxt "mn33:13.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhuṃ saddhā gahapatikā abhihaṭṭhuṃ pavārenti "
"cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārehi, tatra bhikkhu "
"mattaṃ na jānāti paṭiggahaṇāya."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant is invited by a householder to accept robes, alms-"
"food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick, and that mendicant "
"doesn’t know moderation in accepting."

msgctxt "mn33:13.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu anavasesadohī hoti. (10)"
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant milks dry."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya14"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "mn33:14.1"
msgid ""
"Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ye te bhikkhū therā rattaññū cirapabbajitā "
"saṅghapitaro saṅghapariṇāyakā te na atirekapūjāya pūjetā hoti?"
msgstr ""
"And how does a mendicant not show extra respect to senior mendicants of long "
"standing, long gone forth, fathers and leaders of the Saṅgha?"

msgctxt "mn33:14.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ye te bhikkhū therā rattaññū cirapabbajitā "
"saṅghapitaro saṅghapariṇāyakā, tesu na mettaṃ kāyakammaṃ paccupaṭṭhāpeti āvi "
"ceva raho ca;"
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant doesn’t consistently treat senior mendicants of long "
"standing, long gone forth, fathers and leaders of the Saṅgha with kindness "
"by way of body, speech, and mind, both in public and in private."

msgctxt "mn33:14.3"
msgid "na mettaṃ vacīkammaṃ paccupaṭṭhāpeti āvi ceva raho ca;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn33:14.4"
msgid "na mettaṃ manokammaṃ paccupaṭṭhāpeti āvi ceva raho ca."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn33:14.5"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ye te bhikkhū therā rattaññū cirapabbajitā "
"saṅghapitaro saṅghapariṇāyakā te na atirekapūjāya pūjetā hoti. (11)"
msgstr ""
"That’s how a mendicant doesn’t show extra respect to senior mendicants of "
"long standing, long gone forth, fathers and leaders of the Saṅgha."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "mn33:14.6"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho, bhikkhave, ekādasahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu abhabbo imasmiṃ "
"dhammavinaye vuddhiṃ virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ āpajjituṃ."
msgstr ""
"A mendicant with these eleven qualities can’t achieve growth, improvement, "
"or maturity in this teaching and training."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya15"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "mn33:15.1"
msgid ""
"Ekādasahi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgato gopālako bhabbo gogaṇaṃ pariharituṃ "
"phātiṃ kātuṃ."
msgstr "A cowherd with eleven factors can maintain and expand a herd of cattle."

msgctxt "mn33:15.2"
msgid "Katamehi ekādasahi?"
msgstr "What eleven?"

msgctxt "mn33:15.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, gopālako rūpaññū hoti, lakkhaṇakusalo hoti, āsāṭikaṃ hāretā "
"hoti, vaṇaṃ paṭicchādetā hoti, dhūmaṃ kattā hoti, titthaṃ jānāti, pītaṃ "
"jānāti, vīthiṃ jānāti, gocarakusalo hoti, sāvasesadohī ca hoti. Ye te usabhā "
"gopitaro gopariṇāyakā te atirekapūjāya pūjetā hoti."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a cowherd knows form, is skilled in characteristics, picks out "
"flies’ eggs, dresses wounds, smokes out pests, knows the ford, knows when "
"they’re satisfied, knows the trail, is skilled in pastures, doesn’t milk "
"dry, and shows extra respect to the bulls who are fathers and leaders of the "
"herd."

msgctxt "mn33:15.4"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho, bhikkhave, ekādasahi aṅgehi samannāgato gopālako bhabbo gogaṇaṃ "
"pariharituṃ phātiṃ kātuṃ."
msgstr ""
"A cowherd with these eleven factors can maintain and expand a herd of cattle."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya16"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc16"></a>
msgctxt "mn33:16.1"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, bhikkhave, ekādasahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu bhabbo "
"imasmiṃ dhammavinaye vuddhiṃ virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ āpajjituṃ."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, a mendicant with eleven qualities can achieve growth, "
"improvement, and maturity in this teaching and training."

msgctxt "mn33:16.2"
msgid "Katamehi ekādasahi?"
msgstr "What eleven?"

msgctxt "mn33:16.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu rūpaññū hoti, lakkhaṇakusalo hoti, āsāṭikaṃ hāretā "
"hoti, vaṇaṃ paṭicchādetā hoti, dhūmaṃ kattā hoti, titthaṃ jānāti, pītaṃ "
"jānāti, vīthiṃ jānāti, gocarakusalo hoti, sāvasesadohī ca hoti. Ye te "
"bhikkhū therā rattaññū cirapabbajitā saṅghapitaro saṅghapariṇāyakā te "
"atirekapūjāya pūjetā hoti."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant knows form, is skilled in characteristics, picks out "
"flies’ eggs, dresses wounds, smokes out pests, knows the ford, knows "
"satisfaction, knows the trail, is skilled in pastures, doesn’t milk dry, and "
"shows extra respect to senior mendicants of long standing, long gone forth, "
"fathers and leaders of the Saṅgha."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya17"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.223"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc17"></a>
msgctxt "mn33:17.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu rūpaññū hoti?"
msgstr "And how does a mendicant know form?"

msgctxt "mn33:17.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu yaṃ kiñci rūpaṃ sabbaṃ rūpaṃ ‘cattāri mahābhūtāni, "
"catunnañca mahābhūtānaṃ upādāyarūpan’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant truly understands that all form is the four primary "
"elements, or form derived from the four primary elements."

msgctxt "mn33:17.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu rūpaññū hoti. (1)"
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant knows form."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya18"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc18"></a>
msgctxt "mn33:18.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu lakkhaṇakusalo hoti?"
msgstr "And how is a mendicant skilled in characteristics?"

msgctxt "mn33:18.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kammalakkhaṇo bālo, kammalakkhaṇo paṇḍitoti "
"yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant understands that a fool is characterized by their "
"deeds, and an astute person is characterized by their deeds."

msgctxt "mn33:18.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu lakkhaṇakusalo hoti. (2)"
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant is skilled in characteristics."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya19"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc19"></a>
msgctxt "mn33:19.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu āsāṭikaṃ hāretā hoti?"
msgstr "And how does a mendicant pick out flies’ eggs?"

msgctxt "mn33:19.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu uppannaṃ kāmavitakkaṃ nādhivāseti, pajahati "
"vinodeti byantī karoti anabhāvaṃ gameti. Uppannaṃ byāpādavitakkaṃ … pe … "
"uppannaṃ vihiṃsāvitakkaṃ … pe … uppannuppanne pāpake akusale dhamme "
"nādhivāseti, pajahati vinodeti byantī karoti anabhāvaṃ gameti."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant doesn’t tolerate a sensual, malicious, or cruel "
"thought that’s arisen. They don’t tolerate any bad, unskillful qualities "
"that have arisen, but give them up, get rid of them, eliminate them, and "
"obliterate them."

msgctxt "mn33:19.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu āsāṭikaṃ hāretā hoti. (3)"
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant picks out flies’ eggs."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya20"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc20"></a>
msgctxt "mn33:20.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vaṇaṃ paṭicchādetā hoti?"
msgstr "And how does a mendicant dress wounds?"

msgctxt "mn33:20.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā na nimittaggāhī hoti "
"nānubyañjanaggāhī."
msgstr ""
"When a mendicant sees a sight with their eyes, they don’t get caught up in "
"the features and details."

msgctxt "mn33:20.3"
msgid ""
"Yatvādhikaraṇamenaṃ cakkhundriyaṃ asaṃvutaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhādomanassā "
"pāpakā akusalā dhammā anvāssaveyyuṃ tassa saṃvarāya paṭipajjati, rakkhati "
"cakkhundriyaṃ, cakkhundriye saṃvaraṃ āpajjati."
msgstr ""
"If the faculty of sight was left unrestrained, bad unskillful qualities of "
"desire and aversion would become overwhelming. For this reason, they "
"practice restraint, protecting the faculty of sight, and achieving its "
"restraint."

msgctxt "mn33:20.4"
msgid "Sotena saddaṃ sutvā … pe …"
msgstr "When they hear a sound with their ears …"

msgctxt "mn33:20.5"
msgid "ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā … pe …"
msgstr "smell an odor with their nose …"

msgctxt "mn33:20.6"
msgid "jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā … pe …"
msgstr "taste a flavor with their tongue …"

msgctxt "mn33:20.7"
msgid "kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā … pe …"
msgstr "feel a touch with their body …"

msgctxt "mn33:20.8"
msgid "manasā dhammaṃ viññāya na nimittaggāhī hoti nānubyañjanaggāhī."
msgstr ""
"know a thought with their mind, they don’t get caught up in the features and "
"details."

msgctxt "mn33:20.9"
msgid ""
"Yatvādhikaraṇamenaṃ manindriyaṃ asaṃvutaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhādomanassā "
"pāpakā akusalā dhammā anvāssaveyyuṃ tassa saṃvarāya paṭipajjati, rakkhati "
"manindriyaṃ, manindriye saṃvaraṃ āpajjati."
msgstr ""
"If the faculty of mind was left unrestrained, bad unskillful qualities of "
"desire and aversion would become overwhelming. For this reason, they "
"practice restraint, protecting the faculty of mind, and achieving its "
"restraint."

msgctxt "mn33:20.10"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vaṇaṃ paṭicchādetā hoti. (4)"
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant dresses wounds."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya21"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc21"></a>
msgctxt "mn33:21.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dhūmaṃ kattā hoti?"
msgstr "And how does a mendicant smoke out pests?"

msgctxt "mn33:21.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu yathāsutaṃ yathāpariyattaṃ dhammaṃ vitthārena "
"paresaṃ desetā hoti."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant teaches others the Dhamma in detail as they learned "
"and memorized it."

msgctxt "mn33:21.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dhūmaṃ kattā hoti. (5)"
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant smokes out pests."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya22"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc22"></a>
msgctxt "mn33:22.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu titthaṃ jānāti?"
msgstr "And how does a mendicant know the ford?"

msgctxt "mn33:22.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ye te bhikkhū bahussutā āgatāgamā dhammadharā "
"vinayadharā mātikādharā te kālena kālaṃ upasaṅkamitvā paripucchati, "
"paripañhati:"
msgstr ""
"It’s when from time to time a mendicant goes up to those mendicants who are "
"very learned—knowledgeable in the scriptures, who have memorized the "
"teachings, the Vinaya, and the outlines—and asks them questions:"

msgctxt "mn33:22.3"
msgid "‘idaṃ, bhante, kathaṃ?"
msgstr "‘Why, sir, does it say this?"

msgctxt "mn33:22.4"
msgid "Imassa ko attho’ti?"
msgstr "What does that mean?’"

msgctxt "mn33:22.5"
msgid ""
"Tassa te āyasmanto avivaṭañceva vivaranti, anuttānīkatañca uttānīkaronti, "
"anekavihitesu ca kaṅkhāṭhānīyesu dhammesu kaṅkhaṃ paṭivinodenti."
msgstr ""
"Those venerables clarify what is unclear, reveal what is obscure, and dispel "
"doubt regarding the many doubtful matters."

msgctxt "mn33:22.6"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu titthaṃ jānāti. (6)"
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant knows the ford."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya23"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.224"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc23"></a>
msgctxt "mn33:23.1"
msgid "Kathañca bhikkhave, bhikkhu pītaṃ jānāti?"
msgstr "And how does a mendicant know satisfaction?"

msgctxt "mn33:23.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye desiyamāne labhati "
"atthavedaṃ, labhati dhammavedaṃ, labhati dhammūpasaṃhitaṃ pāmojjaṃ."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant, when the teaching and training proclaimed by the "
"Realized One are being taught, finds joy in the meaning and the teaching, "
"and finds joy connected with the teaching."

msgctxt "mn33:23.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu pītaṃ jānāti. (7)"
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant knows satisfaction."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya24"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc24"></a>
msgctxt "mn33:24.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vīthiṃ jānāti?"
msgstr "And how does a mendicant know the trail?"

msgctxt "mn33:24.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti."
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant truly understands the noble eightfold path."

msgctxt "mn33:24.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vīthiṃ jānāti. (8)"
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant knows the trail."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya25"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc25"></a>
msgctxt "mn33:25.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu gocarakusalo hoti?"
msgstr "And how is a mendicant skilled in pastures?"

msgctxt "mn33:25.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cattāro satipaṭṭhāne yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant truly understands the four kinds of mindfulness "
"meditation."

msgctxt "mn33:25.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu gocarakusalo hoti. (9)"
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant is skilled in pastures."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya26"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc26"></a>
msgctxt "mn33:26.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sāvasesadohī hoti?"
msgstr "And how does a mendicant not milk dry?"

msgctxt "mn33:26.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhuṃ saddhā gahapatikā abhihaṭṭhuṃ pavārenti "
"cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārehi."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant is invited by a householder to accept robes, alms-"
"food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick,"

msgctxt "mn33:26.3"
msgid "Tatra bhikkhu mattaṃ jānāti paṭiggahaṇāya."
msgstr "and that mendicant knows moderation in accepting."

msgctxt "mn33:26.4"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sāvasesadohī hoti. (10)"
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant doesn’t milk dry."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya27"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc27"></a>
msgctxt "mn33:27.1"
msgid ""
"Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ye te bhikkhū therā rattaññū cirapabbajitā "
"saṅghapitaro saṅghapariṇāyakā, te atirekapūjāya pūjetā hoti?"
msgstr ""
"And how does a mendicant show extra respect to senior mendicants of long "
"standing, long gone forth, fathers and leaders of the Saṅgha?"

msgctxt "mn33:27.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ye te bhikkhū therā rattaññū cirapabbajitā "
"saṅghapitaro saṅghapariṇāyakā tesu mettaṃ kāyakammaṃ paccupaṭṭhāpeti āvi "
"ceva raho ca;"
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant consistently treats senior mendicants of long "
"standing, long gone forth, fathers and leaders of the Saṅgha with kindness "
"by way of body, speech, and mind, both in public and in private."

msgctxt "mn33:27.3"
msgid "mettaṃ vacīkammaṃ paccupaṭṭhāpeti āvi ceva raho ca;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn33:27.4"
msgid "mettaṃ manokammaṃ paccupaṭṭhāpeti āvi ceva raho ca."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn33:27.5"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ye te bhikkhū therā rattaññū cirapabbajitā "
"saṅghapitaro saṅghapariṇāyakā te atirekapūjāya pūjetā hoti. (11)"
msgstr ""
"That’s how a mendicant shows extra respect to senior mendicants of long "
"standing, long gone forth, fathers and leaders of the Saṅgha."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc28"></a>
msgctxt "mn33:27.6"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho, bhikkhave, ekādasahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu bhabbo imasmiṃ "
"dhammavinaye vuddhiṃ virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ āpajjitun”ti."
msgstr ""
"A mendicant with these eleven qualities can achieve growth, improvement, and "
"maturity in this teaching and training.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc29"></a>
msgctxt "mn33:27.7"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "mn33:27.8"
msgid "Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti."
msgstr "Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn33:27.9"
msgid "Mahāgopālakasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ tatiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
